udience... but with television, the opportunity to meet the fans at Comic Con or any other situation, it''s a chance to enter that circle; it''s that sharing.', 73423, 0), (462349, '''The Voice'' gave me a chance to show people the side of me that is an artist. People didn''t know what that would look like or sound like. It allowed people to see that potential.', 69428, 0), (462350, 'But whether, for example, a coat can be exchanged for twenty yards of linen cloth or for forty yards is not a matter of chance, but depends upon objective conditions, upon the amount of socially necessary labor time contained in the coat and in the linen respectively.', 73424, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (462351, 'I learned the hard way that people are quick to judge, will jump at the chance of a cheap ego boost at another''s expense.', 49182, 0), (462352, 'I look back upon graduate school as being a very happy period in my life. The chance to be thoroughly immersed in physics and to be surrounded by friends pursuing similar goals was a marvelous experience.', 69430, 0), (462353, 'I figure this current era of history is the one with the best chance of quality of life for a black, female, disabled, middle-aged, queer person who''s most comfortable not fitting in. The odds still aren''t great, mind you. But I''ll take my chances with the 21st century.', 7780, 0), (462354, 'One of the fantastic things about books, fiction or non-fiction, is the way they give you a chance to look into different lives.', 40780, 0), (462355, 'One of the values of centering prayer is that you are not thinking about God during the time of centering prayer so you are giving God a chance to manifest. In centering prayer there are moments of peace that give the psyche a chance to realize that God may not be so bad after all. God has a chance to be himself for a change.', 10561, 0), (462356, 'This is a chance for me to listen and learn. There''s no more important and rewarding part of my job.', 73425, 0), (462357, 'A dream will always triumph over reality, once it is given the chance.', 66863, 0), (462358, 'All I demand for the black man is, that the white people shall take their heels off his neck, and let him have a chance to rise by his own efforts.', 73426, 0), (462359, 'Practice every time you get a chance.', 71661, 0), (462360, 'The biggest thing, I think, is to stay healthy and make the fewest mistakes, and then you can win... The margin of error is so small in the NFL, so if you can do those two things - keep your team healthy and make the fewest mistakes each Sunday - you have a good chance of going to the Super Bowl.', 73427, 0), (462361, 'You know you have more to offer, and it gets frustrating when you aren''t given the chance.', 73428, 0), (462362, 'Parikrma aims to give underprivileged children an equal chance at education so they can integrate with kids of private schools and, later, with the society. I want these children to hold high-end jobs at multinational companies and not work at the lower end of the spectrum.', 73429, 0), (462363, 'By giving the public a rich and full melody, distinctly arranged and well played, all the time creating new tone colors and patterns, I feel we have a better chance of being successful. I want a kick to my band, but I don''t want the rhythm to hog the spotlight.', 73430, 0), (462364, 'Well I guess I like variety pretty much, but I do enjoy this work very much. Particularly with Buddy on the gig, we get a chance to knock each other out It''just wonderful.', 73431, 0), (462365, 'Chance is the one thing you can''t buy. You have to pay for it and you have to pay for it with your life, spending a lot of time, you pay for it with time, not the wasting of time but the spending of time.', 73432, 0), (462366, 'If you begin feeling beaten, you will achieve nothing. If you fight, you will perhaps have a chance of achieving something.', 73433, 0), (462367, 'Sometimes people walk into plays by accident - they don''t even know what they''re looking at they just think to give it a chance. That can be the beginning of a long friendship.', 73434, 0), (462368, 'Chance alone is at the source of all novelty, all creation in the biosphere.', 13453, 0), (462369, 'I was a military spouse, and I lived on military pay. It is very difficult to do that. But we do that with honor and with gratitude for the chance to serve this country.', 73435, 0), (462370, 'Unfortunately, we don''t get a second chance. We''ve already played them twice.', 73436, 0), (462371, 'Gratitude makes sense of our past, brings peace for today, and creates a vision for tomorrow.', 1227, 0), (462372, 'Gratitude unlocks the fullness of life. It turns what we have into enough, and more. It turns denial into acceptance, chaos to order, confusion to clarity. It can turn a meal into a feast, a house into a home, a stranger into a friend.', 1227, 0), (462373, 'Be thankful for what you have; you''ll end up having more. If you concentrate on what you don''t have, you will never, ever have enough.', 588, 0), (462374, 'I have a lot to be thankful for. I am healthy, happy and I am loved.', 1356, 0), (462375, 'Make it a habit to tell people thank you. To express your appreciation, sincerely and without the expectation of anything in return. Truly appreciate those around you, and you''ll soon find many others around you. Truly appreciate life, and you''ll find that you have more of it.', 34033, 0), (462376, 'If the only prayer you ever say in your entire life is thank you, it will be enough.', 418, 0), (462377, 'Let me encourage you to get up every day and focus on what you do have in life. Be thankful for the blessings of the little things, even when you don''t get what you expect.', 58655, 0), (462378, 'Whatever we are waiting for - peace of mind, contentment, grace, the inner awareness of simple abundance - it will surely come to us, but only when we are ready to receive it with an open and grateful heart.', 7175, 0), (462379, 'Gratitude is not only the greatest of virtues, but the parent of all the others.', 1306, 0), (462380, 'The thankful receiver bears a plentiful harvest.', 221, 0), (462381, 'Thank you for life, and all the little ups and downs that make it worth living.', 71042, 0), (462382, 'I''m thankful for every moment.', 71940, 0), (462383, 'When I started counting my blessings, my whole life turned around.', 16011, 0), (462384, 'Some people are always grumbling because roses have thorns I am thankful that thorns have roses.', 26458, 0), (462385, 'Gratitude is the fairest blossom which springs from the soul.', 2175, 0), (462386, 'When you are grateful - when you can see what you have - you unlock blessings to flow in your life.', 10090, 0), (462387, 'Gratitude is the sign of noble souls.', 1733, 0), (462388, 'I am what I am thanks to my mother, my father, my brother, my sister... because they have given me everything. The education I have is thanks to them.', 69850, 0), (462389, 'I give all the glory to God. It''s kind of a win-win situation. The glory goes up to Him and the blessings fall down on me.', 66808, 0), (462390, 'Talent is God-given be humble. Fame is man-given be thankful. Conceit is self-given be careful.', 25461, 0), (462391, 'I am even thankful for the negative things that have made me a stronger and better person.', 68480, 0), (462392, 'Let us be grateful to the mirror for revealing to us our appearance only.', 4111, 0), (462393, 'If you suffer, thank God! It is a sure sign that you are alive.', 4, 0), (462394, 'I''m very thankful to all my fans for their constant love and support. I am what I am because of their unconditional love.', 68920, 0), (462395, 'Gratitude is the most exquisite form of courtesy.', 2786, 0), (462396, 'In this world of sin and sorrow there is always something to be thankful for; as for me, I rejoice that I am not a Republican.', 411, 0), (462397, 'I am very thankful and blessed to have a healthy and happy baby boy and baby mama.', 60213, 0), (462398, 'None of us got to where we are alone. Whether the assistance we received was obvious or subtle, acknowledging someone''s help is a big part of understanding the importance of saying thank you.', 25461, 0), (462399, 'No one who achieves success does so without acknowledging the help of others. The wise and confident acknowledge this help with gratitude.', 2606, 0), (462400, 'If you are really thankful, what do you do? You share.', 3433, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (462401, 'Gratitude changes the pangs of memory into a tranquil joy.', 741, 0), (462402, 'Sometimes our light goes out but is blown into flame by another human being. Each of us owes deepest thanks to those who have rekindled this light.', 1006, 0), (462403, 'Keep your eyes open to your mercies. The man who forgets to be thankful has fallen asleep in life.', 449, 0), (462404, 'Be thankful we''re not getting all the government we''re paying for.', 1122, 0), (462405, 'It''s ironic that when you go through a tragedy, you appreciate more. You realize how fragile life is and that there are so many things to still be thankful for.', 14960, 0), (462406, 'Take heed, then, often to come together to give thanks to God, and show forth His praise. For when you assemble frequently in the same place, the powers of Satan are destroyed, and the destruction at which he aims is prevented by the unity of your faith.', 9339, 0), (462407, 'Often people ask how I manage to be happy despite having no arms and no legs. The quick answer is that I have a choice. I can be angry about not having limbs, or I can be thankful that I have a purpose. I chose gratitude.', 1832, 0), (462408, 'No duty is more urgent than that of returning thanks.', 2970, 0), (462409, 'The simple act of saying ''thank you'' is a demonstration of gratitude in response to an experience that was meaningful to a customer or citizen.', 66797, 0), (462410, 'I''m thankful to God that my life changed, but I''m also still on my grind.', 73209, 0), (462411, 'I am thankful for laughter, except when milk comes out of my nose.', 281, 0), (462412, 'We are in a wrong state of mind if we are not in a thankful state of mind.', 36532, 0), (462413, 'I''d like to say to all my fans out there, thanks for the support. And to all my doubters, thank you very much because you guys have also pushed me.', 56473, 0), (462414, 'There''s no happier person than a truly thankful, content person.', 1206, 0), (462415, 'The trick is to be grateful when your mood is high and graceful when it is low.', 3303, 0), (462416, 'Does not the gratitude of the dog put to shame any man who is ungrateful to his benefactors?', 63774, 0), (462417, 'All I ever wanted really, and continue to want out of life, is to give 100 percent to whatever I''m doing and to be committed to whatever I''m doing and then let the results speak for themselves. Also to never take myself or people for granted and always be thankful and grateful to the people who helped me.', 63993, 0), (462418, 'I''m thankful to be breathing, on this side of the grass. Whatever comes, comes.', 68960, 0), (462419, 'It is just that we should be grateful, not only to those with whose views we may agree, but also to those who have expressed more superficial views; for these also contributed something, by developing before us the powers of thought.', 1116, 0), (462420, 'I know that when I pray, something wonderful happens. Not just to the person or persons for whom I''m praying, but also something wonderful happens to me. I''m grateful that I''m heard.', 74, 0), (462421, 'Gratitude is a duty which ought to be paid, but which none have a right to expect.', 1372, 0), (462422, 'For what I have received may the Lord make me truly thankful. And more truly for what I have not received.', 20188, 0), (462423, 'Thanksgiving is a time when the world gets to see just how blessed and how workable the Christian system is. The emphasis is not on giving or buying, but on being thankful and expressing that appreciation to God and to one another.', 70238, 0), (462424, 'Immensely grateful, touched, proud, astonished, abashed.', 925, 0), (462425, 'Be thankful for problems. If they were less difficult, someone with less ability might have your job.', 69860, 0), (462426, 'God has two dwellings; one in heaven, and the other in a meek and thankful heart.', 62724, 0), (462427, 'I wouldn''t change anything. I''ve made mistakes, but thanks to those mistakes, I''ve learned.', 65079, 0), (462428, 'It''s been quite a roller coaster ride, but I''ve grown and learned a lot about myself. The greatest thing is being able to interact with fans and touch people''s lives... for that I give thanks.', 11155, 0), (462429, 'Sometimes we need to remind ourselves that thankfulness is indeed a virtue.', 64156, 0), (462430, 'Whatever life throws at me I''ll take it and be grateful for it as well.', 60164, 0), (462431, 'Drink and be thankful to the host! What seems insignificant when you have it, is important when you need it.', 59853, 0), (462432, 'Never take anything for granted.', 1827, 0), (462433, 'Feeling gratitude isn''t born in us - it''s something we are taught, and in turn, we teach our children.', 5478, 0), (462434, 'It is another''s fault if he be ungrateful, but it is mine if I do not give. To find one thankful man, I will oblige a great many that are not so.', 65434, 0), (462435, 'Every day I''ve got to be thankful that I am alive, and you never know - the cliche is, I guess, you could get hit by a bus tomorrow, so you''d better be at peace with whatever you got going at the moment.', 12986, 0), (462436, 'I have nothing to ask for, thanks to God. Everything I have, God has given me.', 67646, 0), (462437, 'Everything is a blessing, even meetings. Whether it''s meetings or running gassers or lifting, it''s an opportunity, and the best thing to do is be thankful for it.', 73010, 0), (462438, 'I did not break up the Beatles. You can''t have it both ways. If you''re going to blame me for breaking the Beatles up, you should be thankful that I made them into myth rather than a crumbling group.', 1121, 0), (462439, 'I believe that human beings are born first and given passports later. I''m really thankful for my journey. And it''s a journey I didn''t design.', 67527, 0), (462440, 'May those who enjoy the faithful ministry of the Word feel exceedingly thankful for it. There are few blessings on Earth greater for a believer and yet the Lord is frequently obliged to teach us the value of this blessing by depriving us of it for a season.', 19001, 0), (462441, 'If a fellow isn''t thankful for what he''s got, he isn''t likely to be thankful for what he''s going to get.', 27528, 0), (462442, 'It''s important you stay professional and keep working, and I''m thankful for everything that''s happened to me.', 67080, 0), (462443, 'I am what I am, I''m doing very well in my life, and I''m thankful to God for that.', 68084, 0), (462444, 'I''m grateful for always this moment, the now, no matter what form it takes.', 378, 0), (462445, 'I do not so much rejoice that God hath made me to be a Queen, as to be a Queen over so thankful a people.', 1401, 0), (462446, 'The unthankful heart... discovers no mercies; but let the thankful heart sweep through the day and, as the magnet finds the iron, so it will find, in every hour, some heavenly blessings!', 2175, 0), (462447, 'We can be thankful to a friend for a few acres, or a little money; and yet for the freedom and command of the whole earth, and for the great benefits of our being, our life, health, and reason, we look upon ourselves as under no obligation.', 65434, 0), (462448, 'Those who give themselves to prayer should in a special manner have always a devotion to St. Joseph; for I know not how any man can think of the Queen of the angels, during the time that she suffered so much with the Infant Jesus, without giving thanks to St. Joseph for the services he rendered them then.', 69044, 0), (462449, 'When you solve a problem, you ought to thank God and go on to the next one.', 62560, 0), (462450, 'Should it happen tomorrow, I would fall to my knees to give thanks to God for such a career.', 69946, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (462451, 'When you read a piece of writing that you admire, send a note of thanks to the author.', 360, 0), (462452, 'Of all the characteristics needed for both a happy and morally decent life, none surpasses gratitude. Grateful people are happier, and grateful people are more morally decent.', 4608, 0), (462453, 'I was successful materially, but I know life is much more than worldly success. I saw all these blessings God had given me. The way to give thanks is obedience to God.', 67939, 0), (462454, 'We can always find something to be thankful for, and there may be reasons why we ought to be thankful for even those dispensations which appear dark and frowning.', 72587, 0), (462455, 'It is okay to be an outsider, a recent arrival, new on the scene - and not just okay, but something to be thankful for... Because being an insider can so easily mean collapsing the horizons, can so easily mean accepting the presumptions of your province.', 73437, 0), (462456, 'I had the pleasure, as Robin said, to live a childhood dream as many young Americans and Puerto Rican children live that play youth baseball. And I feel honored and very thankful for that opportunity.', 69692, 0), (462457, 'If I could write a story that would do for the Indian one-hundredth part what ''Uncle Tom''s Cabin'' did for the Negro, I would be thankful the rest of my life.', 25904, 0), (462458, 'Those men and women are fortunate who are born at a time when a great struggle for human freedom is in progress. It is an added good fortune to have parents who take a personal part in the great movements of their time. I am glad and thankful that this was my case.', 16347, 0), (462459, 'Just don''t let the hype of what people are saying and how much they love you, y''know, just take the compliment and be thankful that people are complimenting you, but don''t let it consume you; don''t let your circumstances around you and the way people view you make you act a certain way.', 47442, 0), (462460, 'At Thanksgiving, I always start at the top of my list and say I''m grateful for friends, family, and good health. Then I get more superficial... like being thankful for my Louboutins.', 63466, 0), (462461, 'Before I get out of bed, I am saying thank you. I know how important it is to be thankful.', 5315, 0), (462462, 'In my case, my mother had to be my mother and father, so I am thankful to her.', 68274, 0), (462463, 'I''m thankful for each and every day. We never know when time is up.', 67724, 0), (462464, 'I''m very thankful to directors and filmmakers who consider me in their films, and I hope I''m able to do justice to their films.', 68907, 0), (462465, 'I''m thankful for performing as long as I am allowed.', 67724, 0), (462466, 'My biggest fear ever is to be involved in a plane crash, so when that happened... well, I''m just thankful to be alive. I''m just grateful to be here at all.', 71042, 0), (462467, 'I''m very humbled and honored. I''m very thankful to the Asian-American Community for all their support!', 69766, 0), (462468, 'Thankfully, we didn''t stop at Malta. I think Malta was thankful, too.', 7873, 0), (462469, 'As a child, I didn''t know what I didn''t have. I''m thankful for the challenges early on in my life because now I have a perspective on the world and kind of know what''s important.', 70719, 0), (462470, 'I''m thankful for my songs being at the top of the charts but I am human - I think people still have to remember that.', 72233, 0), (462471, 'I dreamed about this as a kid, that I would write - and people would read - a whole series of books. I feel accomplished, giddy, and tired. Mostly, though, I feel thankful. A trilogy is a huge investment on the part of author, publisher, and reader, and I''m grateful that so many people were willing to invest along with me.', 785, 0), (462472, 'I''m thankful because all the hard work and sacrifices were worth it in the end.', 73438, 0), (462473, 'I am really excited and thankful for opportunity to work with Cotto Promotions, Tidal and Roc Nation.', 73439, 0), (462474, 'It feels great to win and I can''t be more thankful to the Lord for walking me through every step. God was and is so faithful every time.', 73440, 0), (462475, 'I''m thankful for weird people out there ''cause they''re some of the most creative people.', 68275, 0), (462476, 'I''m thankful to have time to write.', 21274, 0), (462477, 'Every Thanksgiving, we all write down three things we''re thankful for and put them in a hat. Then we pass the hat around the dinner table and everyone has to guess who wrote what!', 70283, 0), (462478, 'Charity never humiliated him who profited from it, nor ever bound him by the chains of gratitude, since it was not to him but to God that the gift was made.', 69, 0), (462479, 'When a person doesn''t have gratitude, something is missing in his or her humanity.', 10, 0), (462480, 'As with all commandments, gratitude is a description of a successful mode of living. The thankful heart opens our eyes to a multitude of blessings that continually surround us.', 9153, 0), (462481, 'I want to be as gracious and thankful as I can because it has been a long road.', 68246, 0), (462482, 'I''m a human just like anyone else. We all have our problems that we deal with on and off the field. I''m thankful to have a beautiful wife and child that can help ease those problems when you come home.', 73441, 0), (462483, 'Many of our prayers were not answered, and for this we are now grateful.', 5249, 0), (462484, 'Such lovely warmth of thought and delicacy of colour are beyond all praise, and equally beyond all thanks!', 23403, 0), (462485, 'We in the United States should be all the more thankful for the freedom and religious tolerance we enjoy. And we should always remember the lessons learned from the Holocaust, in hopes we stay vigilant against such inhumanity now and in the future.', 73442, 0), (462486, 'Fame is a funny thing. I like doing normal things. I like going to fairs. I like going to ball games. I like going to Disney World or a big field on the Fourth of July and having picnics with friends. The problem is you''re either worried you''re going to be recognized, or you''re thankful you''re not. It''s always there.', 23824, 0), (462487, 'I feel like I''m doing what I love. If I can get out, shoot, film and climb, and be with my friends and family, I''m happy. It doesn''t take a lot. I don''t need to climb huge mountains. I have a deep connection with wilderness and the environment, and I''m thankful for that.', 30158, 0), (462488, 'A single grateful thought toward heaven is the most perfect prayer.', 3244, 0), (462489, 'Thank God we''re living in a country where the sky''s the limit, the stores are open late and you can shop in bed thanks to television.', 17330, 0), (462490, 'All our discontents about what we want appeared to spring from the want of thankfulness for what we have.', 15620, 0), (462491, 'I''m thankful to have Jesus as my Savior. My relationship with God has always been one to where I''m talking to him all day, every day, about anything and everything. It''s just a continuous ongoing conversation that I have with the Lord, and I feel like that''s brought me closer to Him.', 69758, 0), (462492, 'I''m thankful for the three ounce Ziploc bag, so that I have somewhere to put my savings.', 6225, 0), (462493, 'Years ago, it was pretty hard to get people to empathize even a little bit with scaly, cold-blooded critters; now, thanks a lot to good PR from television, it is easier to get the message of reptile conservation and tolerance across. We have a lot to be thankful to reptiles for, not the least of which is their control of rodents.', 73443, 0), (462494, 'My mother is such an incredibly strong woman. She raised a family of five boys extremely well. She made us all strong, loving, caring people. We all support each other. I''m really thankful to her.', 68865, 0), (462495, 'I don''t know about changing my perspective, because motherhood is such a glorious blessing and I am very thankful for that. It''s such a beautiful experience. I so strongly recommend it. It''s bliss, love and fulfillment of another level.', 68393, 0), (462496, 'My mother had abandoned the family, so grandmother raised me. And she was instrumental in that she taught me that the world is a glorious place. She taught me to embrace humanity. And she''d say there''s never an excuse for joy. And to be thankful.', 67627, 0), (462497, 'I think being raised spending so much time outdoors was really important - while you''re in it, you might not know, but now I think of the things I was thankful for.', 7655, 0), (462498, 'I realized this is what God has dealt me, and I should be thankful considering all that''s happened to me in my life, but MS caused the movies to stop - stop dead - and I miss it.', 2259, 0), (462499, 'If I''m not working, I have home time with my family, and if I spend that stressing what''s going to happen next, then it''s a waste. I have a lot to be thankful for.', 73444, 0), (462500, 'Thanks to the Interstate Highway System, it is now possible to travel across the country from coast to coast without seeing anything.', 37230, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (462501, 'Dear Lord, I''m so grateful I''m still loved.', 61597, 0), (462502, 'I''m definitely aware that the physical appearance is a very temporary gift. I''m very thankful for the opportunities that I''ve been able to experience, but I keep it all in check and don''t let it consume me.', 69673, 0), (462503, 'I''m thankful for the incredible advances in medicine that have taken place during my lifetime. I almost certainly wouldn''t still be here if it weren''t for them.', 4008, 0), (462504, 'A proud man is seldom a grateful man, for he never thinks he gets as much as he deserves.', 2175, 0), (462505, 'I am thankful, of course, for the prize and thankful to God for each story, each idea, each word, each day.', 1467, 0), (462506, 'Every one of our greatest national treasures, our liberty, enterprise, vitality, wealth, military power, global authority, flow from a surprising source: our ability to give thanks.', 72452, 0), (462507, 'We sing a little song before we eat, a little blessing before we eat, and it''s really - we''re thanking the Lord and the Earth for the food that we eat, and it really brings you together in a profound kind of way.', 41030, 0), (462508, 'I''m thankful for the ability to share my faith in a lot of different places. It''s something that I take as a responsibility and an obligation to handle as best as I can.', 4052, 0), (462509, 'I''m thankful I grew up the way I did. It made me a hard worker and insightful to other people''s lives.', 66619, 0), (462510, 'I realize how unique my path has been. And I''m thankful for that.', 69939, 0), (462511, 'The ''Night Train'' has already been a crazy ride for me. We flew around making TV appearances and stadium announcements all over the country, fueled by little more than coffee and adrenaline... so many fans jumped on board with us, and I couldn''t be more thankful.', 22996, 0), (462512, 'My relationship with God is what gives me a moral compass on what decisions to make and that stuff. I''m thankful that I have the people around me that I do, and they remind me each day of who I am and what I stand for.', 73445, 0), (462513, 'We can be thankful President Barack Obama is taking aim at one of the prime causes of climate change and extreme weather: air pollution. The EPA''s carbon pollution standards are the most significant step forward our country has ever taken to protect our health by addressing climate change.', 67006, 0), (462514, 'I''m proud - or really more thankful than anything - for all the work that I''ve gotten.', 72302, 0), (462515, 'You can think you''re living in the moment and you''re thankful, but when somebody comes face to face with you and says, ''I just lost my child,'' or ''I have months to live, and thank you...'' I''m of course sad for them, but I''m thankful that I gave them a gift and they''re giving me a gift.', 67056, 0), (462516, 'There was no instruction to be thankful that the Christians were special people, chosen people. There was no nationalistic, political or ethnic superiority to be thankful for.', 70238, 0), (462517, 'I am both honored and blessed to have had such a wonderful career with the L.A. Galaxy and I am thankful for everything the club, the fans and the community has done for me and my family.', 72841, 0), (462518, 'I''m thankful enough or blessed enough to be able to say that Miles Davis was a friend when he was alive, and he was a wonderful mentor and really, really funny, you know.', 12819, 0), (462519, 'I''m just thankful to be blessed with my talent.', 68262, 0), (462520, 'I''m thankful for all the things that this job has given me and my family. But probably the thing that I am most proud of throughout my career is that, not only myself, but my family and the people around me have just been regular people, which we are.', 68939, 0), (462521, 'I wouldn''t be where I am without my fans, and I am very thankful for them.', 69357, 0), (462522, 'I actually feel I''m in a much better place than I''ve ever been because I''m thankful people still love the songs that I''ve written, and they seem to like me. And they come to the shows in droves, and they get all excited, and I can still hit all the notes, and I don''t look terrible.', 73446, 0), (462523, 'My fans are definitely my shareholders, and I''m extremely thankful for them.', 73447, 0), (462524, 'I am just so thankful that my mom was a fantastic mom. She wasn''t a stage mother she didn''t push me. She was happy if I was happy. We are so different. I was very shy my mom did all the talking. She was my strength. She never expected that I would be this ballerina. ', 68311, 0), (462525, 'I''m thankful for not ever taking anything illegal.', 67926, 0), (462526, 'Unfortunately, I''m not 185 and 6-3 and can run and catch fade routes all game. I do the dirty work. I''m all good. I''m thankful for it. Somebody''s got to do it.', 73448, 0), (462527, 'I feel very, very thankful to have the family that I do.', 69499, 0), (462528, 'I''m grateful for the opportunities God gave me to minister to people in high places; people in power have spiritual and personal needs like everyone else, and often they have no one to talk to.', 4008, 0), (462529, 'I''m very thankful that I can make people happy just by signing my name.', 1121, 0), (462530, 'Look folks, we know who built this country and we know who is going to rebuild it. It''s you. Instead of vilifying you, we should be thanking you. We owe you.', 17532, 0), (462531, 'There is such a thing as ''thanks-feeling'' - feeling thankful. This ought to be the general, universal spirit of the Christian.', 36532, 0), (462532, 'I think everything is going to be devastatingly sad - when the phone rings, I know somebody in my family''s been hurt, somebody''s going to die. I''m sure a therapist would go, ''That''s not a good way to live,'' but every time it''s not that bad thing, I''m so thankful and appreciative.', 68422, 0), (462533, 'I''m thankful that I was able to have a long, healthy career for the most part.', 73449, 0), (462534, 'I have got good films, and I am thankful to Aditya Chopra. He put a lot of faith in me.', 66951, 0), (462535, 'I''m so thankful to have been born in the times that we live in.', 69499, 0), (462536, 'Music is very powerful and can make you feel whatever it is. If you listen to gospel, you''re going to feel thankful, and you''re going to want to call up people that you hate and tell them that you love them. When you listen to sexual music, it gets you in the mood.', 2025, 0), (462537, 'God has blessed me with an unbelievable talent, with fast feet, fast hands, unbelievable defense and a very, very sharp mind. So I''m thankful for that.', 67644, 0), (462538, 'I am a big defender of ''Harry Potter,'' and I think any book that gets kids to read are books that we should cherish, we should be thankful for them.', 1041, 0), (462539, 'If you reflect often on how His Atonement has changed you, and if you give thanks often, you will find that your witness of Him gains power to touch the hearts of others. When those you invite out of your own testimony feel that witness, they will come to accept Him as their Lord and Savior.', 9158, 0), (462540, 'I''m really thankful for every experience I''ve had, even the ones that were puzzling or disorienting, because they taught me so much.', 32663, 0), (462541, 'Unseasonable kindness gets no thanks.', 1348, 0), (462542, 'Well, there''s not a day goes by when I don''t get up and say thank you to somebody.', 44554, 0), (462543, 'I''m happy with who I am inside. I''d hate to have accolades and all that and not really be happy with who I was. So I''m really thankful for my family and for the support system that I have for being the person that I am today. I''m proud of who I am.', 68249, 0), (462544, 'I''m very happy that major players are always giving their opinions about my life, my game. I am very thankful for that.', 73450, 0), (462545, 'Why I got into music was James Taylor, so to see him be a real down-to-earth guy that''s unbelievably talented... then to hear him sing those lyrics of ''What I''m Thankful For,'' which is a song Ms. Yearwood and I got to write together, that was definitely a highlight of my recording life.', 56259, 0), (462546, 'I''m very thankful to be doing what I''m doing. I feel very blessed.', 58477, 0), (462547, 'I''m just really, really thankful. I''m thankful to the doctors; I''m thankful to the family that donated the kidney.', 68922, 0), (462548, 'I''ve been blessed in that regard through and through. So I''m just thankful for this opportunity to play the game that I love and share that with the world.', 69121, 0), (462549, 'I kind of just write what I like to write. I''m thankful that readers of different ages seem to connect to my stories. I don''t consciously think about age demographics when I''m working on my comics.', 16732, 0), (462550, 'Anytime that another artist or a critic that is well-respected says something nice about you, you''re always thankful and hope that you can live up to that.', 66588, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (462551, 'To do what I love every day and have the support of the fans, it does not happen like this all the time, so it is important to be thankful... I know it doesn''t last forever, and we have to get it while we can.', 67360, 0), (462552, 'I think there is no racism in this film industry. They are only in need of talent, though it takes time; but, if you are talented, you will get your due. I am thankful to be part of this industry.', 68260, 0), (462553, 'I''m happy and thankful that people are messing with the Dolla $ign.', 68262, 0), (462554, 'I''m thankful I am able to continue to share the joy and the inspiration tap brings.', 71240, 0), (462555, 'I was a filmy kid. I was two when I faced the camera for the first time. My parents realised it pretty early, and I''m really thankful to them for their support and help.', 68929, 0), (462556, 'There''s definitely no hard feelings with WWE. I''m very thankful to them for the opportunity that was given to me.', 67038, 0), (462557, 'I''ve been very close to Konnan for many years now. I thank him for much of my success in this industry. He opened the doors for me in AAA, ECW, and WCW. I''m very thankful.', 67038, 0), (462558, 'We''ve always had each other''s backs in and out of competition. We support each other the most because we''re the only ones that know what it''s like to go through what we do, and so we can''t be more thankful for each other. We''re like sisters.', 72055, 0), (462559, 'I am incredibly thankful for the strong support I have from my peers in the industry and of course my amazing fans.', 36193, 0), (462560, 'I found out that superstars Winkler and William Shatner are real people, and I was so thankful for that.', 67040, 0), (462561, 'We are just so thankful that Christ does not measure us by what we do. God is not measuring us by that, He is measuring us by our faith in Christ.', 69736, 0), (462562, 'You can expect nothing in being a musician, and you have to be just very thankful every time it goes positively for you.', 60183, 0), (462563, 'When I started acting, I thought if I got one or two jobs a year I''d be lucky. So yeah, my career has gone so much farther than I ever suspected it would, and as such I feel lucky for everything I get. I feel thankful and grateful.', 70221, 0), (462564, 'I was in the postseason twice and I''m thankful for that.', 66959, 0), (462565, 'I''m very thankful I''m very appreciative for everything that the Denver Broncos organization has done for me.', 67866, 0), (462566, 'I have a fine level of recognition in the business and among the acting community now, so I consider myself one of the lucky ones. If I didn''t think that, there would be something wrong with me. I''m grateful and thankful for what I''ve got.', 8605, 0), (462567, 'I am really thankful to the audiences that they have appreciated all my songs and I have managed to touch their soul.', 67868, 0), (462568, 'That''s what I love about my faith and Christianity. It''s the polar opposite of darn near everything I experienced in the wrestling business. I still love the business, and I''m thankful for everything that it''s provided, but the idea that it deals in the truth is the furthest thing from reality.', 36579, 0), (462569, 'I learn more with every job, and I''m very thankful for where I am.', 33023, 0), (462570, 'Most people repent their sins by thanking God they ain''t so wicked as their neighbors.', 3355, 0), (462571, 'It was a free-for-all with music when I was growing up. My mother was a huge music fanatic so I was listening to everything from country to heavy metal to Indigo Girls to Elton John. I guess when I was really young I didn''t like Willie Nelson, and she obviously loved him. Now I do too, I''m so thankful to her for playing his music nonstop.', 67056, 0), (462572, 'I''m so thankful that there are people willing to do that - to actually carry a child nine months for someone.', 69131, 0), (462573, 'My fans have made all my career moments special for me. They are the ones that have gotten me through every single thing - good times and bad, they are who I go to and lean on. I am very thankful for that.', 3263, 0), (462574, 'I know how I want to operate as an artist. And that is by having an honest, genuine dialogue about this kind of screwed up journey I''ve had that I''m so thankful for.', 67060, 0), (462575, 'I want to let my fans get to know a little about me. I''m very thankful for everything they''ve done for me so, of course, I''m going to let them into my world a bit. But I really am a very private person, and I love kepping my life to myself - that''s how I''ve always been.', 67817, 0), (462576, 'Thankfully, while our self-righteousness reaches far, God''s grace reaches farther.', 16728, 0), (462577, 'There''s no ex out there who I''m not friends with today, and I''m extremely thankful for that.', 69198, 0), (462578, 'While the women of the older generation were thankful if only they succeeded in obtaining ''a work and a duty,'' however monotonous and wearing it might be, the will of the younger generation for a pleasurable labour has fortunately increased.', 62381, 0), (462579, 'The only jobs kids have are to do well in school, to be charming and polite, and be thankful. That''s it. I''ll house you, protect you, I''ll even give my life for you, and in return, you will behave.', 11192, 0), (462580, 'The first thing I do when I start my day is, I get down on my hands and knees and give thanks to God. Whenever I go outside of my house, the first thing I do is stop at the church.', 13187, 0), (462581, 'I get along very well with the cast of ''30 Rock.'' I guess I bring a certain quirkiness to the show as well. I''m just thankful they keep asking me. I didn''t think I was going to be asked back so every time they say, ''We want you back,'' I''m screaming. I''m jumping up and down and screaming.', 73210, 0), (462582, 'If you sell the film rights to your 