 in your life.', 52414, 0), (463043, 'The God of the Hebrews is a God that human language, we''re not even supposed to speak the holy name. We were told in the Second Commandment we could make no images of this God, and I don''t think that means just building idols, I think that means also trying to believe you''ve captured God in your words, in the Creeds, in the Scriptures.', 21548, 0), (463044, 'In the Lord''s Prayer, the first petition is for daily bread. No one can worship God or love his neighbor on an empty stomach.', 1970, 0), (463045, 'Sorrow for sin is indeed necessary, but it should not be an endless preoccupation. You must dwell also on the glad remembrance of God''s loving-kindness; otherwise, sadness will harden the heart and lead it more deeply into despair.', 65719, 0), (463046, 'Because I believe in God and have faith in God, it doesn''t mean I am immortal. It doesn''t mean I am immune, as has been claimed. I am as scared as anyone of getting hurt, especially driving a Formula One car.', 31997, 0), (463047, 'If you hug to yourself any resentment against anybody else, you destroy the bridge by which God would come to you.', 2148, 0), (463048, 'Laughter is God''s blessing.', 52414, 0), (463049, 'There is one God, and He made both Indians and white men. We were all made out of the dust of the earth.', 70864, 0), (463050, 'I just want to do God''s will. And he''s allowed me to go to the mountain. And I''ve looked over, and I''ve seen the promised land! I may not get there with you, but I want you to know tonight that we as a people will get to the promised land.', 21767, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (463051, 'If I am capable of grasping God objectively, I do not believe, but precisely because I cannot do this I must believe.', 3131, 0), (463052, 'Marriage has made me a lot happier and I''m deeply in love with my wife, and I thank God for her every day.', 68271, 0), (463053, 'God does not change; he is Love, ever and always. In himself, he is communion, unity in Trinity, and all his words and works are directed to communion.', 856, 0), (463054, 'I have sworn upon the altar of God, eternal hostility against every form of tyranny over the mind of man.', 1207, 0), (463055, 'The essence of Hinduism is the same essence of all true religions: Bhakti or pure love for God and genuine compassion for all beings.', 26105, 0), (463056, 'God is a verb, not a noun.', 11496, 0), (463057, 'Knowledge of God''s Word is a bulwark against deception, temptation, accusation, even persecution.', 12361, 0), (463058, 'God always strives together with those who strive.', 1882, 0), (463059, 'And God said, ''Let there be light'' and there was light, but the Electricity Board said He would have to wait until Thursday to be connected.', 7873, 0), (463060, 'There''s too much tendency to attribute to God the evils that man does of his own free will.', 94, 0), (463061, 'But at any rate, the point is that God is what nobody admits to being, and everybody really is.', 45466, 0), (463062, 'God, life changes faster than you think.', 1039, 0), (463063, 'I''m an atheist and I thank God for it.', 266, 0), (463064, 'The limitless loving devotion to God, and the gift God makes of Himself to you, are the highest elevation of which the heart is capable; it is the highest degree of prayer. The souls that have reached this point are truly the heart of the Church.', 73510, 0), (463065, 'I am convinced that God wanted me to be a baseball player.', 72845, 0), (463066, 'Whatsoever is, is in God, and without God nothing can be, or be conceived.', 2478, 0), (463067, 'Our national motto is ''In God we Trust,'' reminding us that faith in our Creator is the most important American value of all.', 66707, 0), (463068, 'The Gospel is about grace and we all know that grace is about us receiving from God blessings that we don''t deserve.', 13570, 0), (463069, 'Any fool knows that bravado is always a cover-up for insecurity. That''s the truth. And on that note, I''ll say goodnight. God love you.', 21395, 0), (463070, 'There''s only one effectively redemptive sacrifice, the sacrifice of self-will to make room for the knowledge of God.', 1032, 0), (463071, 'God is the tangential point between zero and infinity.', 19815, 0), (463072, 'It may be that our role on this planet is not to worship God - but to create him.', 1004, 0), (463073, 'God, I can push the grass apart and lay my finger on Thy heart.', 106, 0), (463074, 'God has entrusted me with myself.', 1328, 0), (463075, 'God hangs the greatest weights upon the smallest wires.', 1035, 0), (463076, 'One and God make a majority.', 7432, 0), (463077, 'Nobody talks so constantly about God as those who insist that there is no God.', 9835, 0), (463078, 'Life is God''s novel. Let him write it.', 1467, 0), (463079, 'God is an unutterable sigh, planted in the depths of the soul.', 62538, 0), (463080, 'It is only the impossible that is possible for God. He has given over the possible to the mechanics of matter and the autonomy of his creatures.', 1662, 0), (463081, 'God gets you to the plate, but once your there your on your own.', 9815, 0), (463082, 'In almost everything that touches our everyday life on earth, God is pleased when we''re pleased. He wills that we be as free as birds to soar and sing our maker''s praise without anxiety.', 73511, 0), (463083, 'God''s truth judges created things out of love, and Satan''s truth judges them out of envy and hatred.', 741, 0), (463084, 'However many blessings we expect from God, His infinite liberality will always exceed all our wishes and our thoughts.', 4271, 0), (463085, 'There is no work, however vile or sordid, that does not glisten before God.', 4271, 0), (463086, 'Trust in God - she will provide.', 16347, 0), (463087, 'Even God lends a hand to honest boldness.', 31012, 0), (463088, 'God is looking for people to use, and if you can get usable, he will wear you out. The most dangerous prayer you can pray is this: ''Use me.''', 710, 0), (463089, 'The way to be with God in every season is to strive to be near Him every week and each day.', 327, 0), (463090, 'We should always look upon ourselves as God''s servants, placed in God''s world, to do his work; and accordingly labour faithfully for him; not with a design to grow rich and great, but to glorify God, and do all the good we possibly can.', 67770, 0), (463091, 'I''m grateful to God for His bountiful gifts... He gave me courage and faith in myself.', 44815, 0), (463092, 'Great and glorious God, and Thou Lord Jesus, I pray you shed abroad your light in the darkness of my mind. Be found of me, Lord, so that in all things I may act only in accordance with Thy holy will.', 1681, 0), (463093, 'To doubt God is to doubt one''s own conscience, and in consequence, it would be to doubt everything; and then what is life for?', 3961, 0), (463094, 'God put the human race in charge of managing the resources of the entire planet for the benefit of all life. Therefore, we, of all people on this planet, should be concerned about environmental issues and doing what we can to enhance the beauty and productivity of the natural realm.', 50423, 0), (463095, 'We say keep your change, we''ll keep our God, our guns, our constitution.', 4221, 0), (463096, 'Like the old soldier of the ballad, I now close my military career and just fade away, an old soldier who tried to do his duty as God gave him the light to see that duty. Goodbye.', 2273, 0), (463097, 'You never know God is all you need until God is all you have.', 710, 0), (463098, 'God made and governs the world invisibly, and has commanded us to love and worship him and no other God; to honor our parents and masters, and love our neighbours as ourselves; and to be temperate, just, and peaceable, and to be merciful even to brute beasts.', 2482, 0), (463099, 'I have never made but one prayer to God, a very short one: ''O Lord make my enemies ridiculous.'' And God granted it.', 808, 0), (463100, 'Fix reason firmly in her seat, and call to her tribunal every fact, every opinion. Question with boldness even the existence of a God; because, if there be one, he must more approve of the homage of reason, than that of blindfolded fear.', 1207, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (463101, 'No man ever did, nor ever shall, truly go forth to convert the nations, nor to prophesy in the present state of witnesses against Antichrist, but by the gracious inspiration and instigation of the Holy Spirit of God.', 57393, 0), (463102, 'We cannot suppose therefore that God has made an order of beings, with such mental qualities and powers, for the sole purpose of being used as beasts, or instruments of labour.', 73361, 0), (463103, 'But separation of church and state was never meant to separate God and government.', 66757, 0), (463104, 'To do all that one is able to do, is to be a man; to do all that one would like to do, is to be a god.', 1702, 0), (463105, 'The key to winning is choosing to do God''s will and loving others with all you''ve got.', 2081, 0), (463106, 'Here''s the reality. The image of a white Jesus has been used to justify enslavement, conquest, colonialism, the genocide of indigenous peoples. There are literally millions of human beings whose lives have been snuffed out by people who conquered under the banner of a white god.', 24606, 0), (463107, 'Sense perceptions can be and often are false and deceptive, however real they may appear to us. Where there is realization outside the senses, it is infallible. It is proved not by extraneous evidence but in the transformed conduct and character of those who have felt the real presence of God within.', 32, 0), (463108, 'People who cease to believe in God or goodness altogether still believe in the devil. I don''t know why. No, I do indeed know why. Evil is always possible. And goodness is eternally difficult.', 618, 0), (463109, 'But suppose God is black? What if we go to Heaven and we, all our lives, have treated the Negro as an inferior, and God is there, and we look up and He is not white? What then is our response?', 60667, 0), (463110, 'God gave me a great body and it''s my duty to take care of my physical temple.', 69380, 0), (463111, 'I''m gonna be blunt and plain, if one ever looks at me like that I''m gonna kill him and tell God he died.', 73512, 0), (463112, 'No enactment of man can be considered law unless it conforms to the law of God.', 73513, 0), (463113, 'The main rule to me is to honor God with your life. To life a life of integrity. Not be selfish. You know, help others. But that''s really the essence of the Christian faith.', 3956, 0), (463114, 'May God protect me from gloomy saints.', 69044, 0), (463115, 'Only the supernatural love of God through changed lives can solve the problems that we face in our world.', 4008, 0), (463116, 'Man is important in one sense only. He was made in the image of God: That is his importance. He is not important for his body, ego, or personality. His constant affirmation of ego-consciousness is the source of all his problems.', 2055, 0), (463117, 'We are not sent into this world mainly to enjoy the loveliness therein, nor to sit us down in passive ease; no, we were sent here for action. The soul that seeks to do the will of God with a pure heart, fervently, does not yield to the lethargy of ease.', 3921, 0), (463118, 'God made man to go by motives, and he will not go without them, any more than a boat without steam or a balloon without gas.', 2175, 0), (463119, 'Law and equity are two things which God has joined, but which man has put asunder.', 432, 0), (463120, 'I do not want to foresee the future. I am concerned with taking care of the present. God has given me no control over the moment following.', 32, 0), (463121, 'You''re just left with yourself all the time, whatever you do anyway. You''ve got to get down to your own God in your own temple. It''s all down to you, mate.', 46, 0), (463122, 'When we believe that God is Father, we also believe that such a father''s hand will never cause his child a needless tear. We may not understand life any better, but we will not resent life any longer.', 18978, 0), (463123, 'The Church is the new creation, it is life and joy, it is the sacramental fellowship in which we share the ultimate purpose of God, made real for us now in our hearing the Word and sharing the Sacrament.', 9221, 0), (463124, 'Anytime you deny the acknowledgement of God you are undermining the entire basis for which our country exists.', 66757, 0), (463125, 'This is why the ultimate reason of things must lie in a necessary substance, in which the differentiation of the changes only exists eminently as in their source; and this is what we call God.', 70838, 0), (463126, 'The all-seeing eye of God beheld our deplorable state infinite pity touched the heart of the Father of mercies and infinite wisdom laid the plan of our recovery.', 67770, 0), (463127, 'Order is manifestly maintained in the universe... governed by the sovereign will of God.', 48987, 0), (463128, 'For God''s sake hold your tongue, and let me love.', 703, 0), (463129, 'I can''t believe that God put us on this earth to be ordinary.', 2081, 0), (463130, 'Earth''s crammed with heaven, And every common bush afire with God: But only he who sees takes off his shoes.', 157, 0), (463131, 'God does not begin by asking our ability, only our availability, and if we prove our dependability, He will increase our capability.', 2051, 0), (463132, 'If God only used perfect people, nothing would get done. God will use anybody if you''re available.', 710, 0), (463133, 'Thank God for acupuncture. It''s been around for 2000 years. It''s not going anyplace and people use it all of the time for a variety of cures and to avoid illnesses.', 37938, 0), (463134, 'The only answer to fear is faith in God, knowing He loves you unconditionally and individually.', 1206, 0), (463135, 'The Christian leader of the future is called to be completely irrelevant and to stand in this world with nothing to offer but his or her own vulnerable self. God loves us, not because of what we do or accomplish, but because God has created and redeemed us in love.', 19097, 0), (463136, 'Each of you is a unique child of God. God knows you individually. He sends messages of encouragement, correction, and direction fitted to you and to your needs.', 9158, 0), (463137, 'My mother always used to say, ''Well, if you had been born a little girl growing up in Egypt, you would go to church or go to worship Allah, but surely if those people are worshipping a God, it must be the same God'' - that''s what she always said. The same God with different names.', 2086, 0), (463138, 'There is no uncreated being except God. God has no opposite.', 26, 0), (463139, 'Let God''s grace be the mosque, and devotion the prayer mat. Let the Quran be the good conduct.', 4201, 0), (463140, 'There are worlds and more worlds below them, and there are a hundred thousand skies over them. No one has been able to find the limits and boundaries of God. If there be any account of God, then alone the mortal can write the same; but God''s account does not finish, and the mortal himself dies while still writing.', 4201, 0), (463141, 'I wish that the Indians believed me a god, for upon the report of an enemy''s valor oftentimes depends the success of a battle, and false reports have many times done as great things as true courage and resolution.', 7819, 0), (463142, 'Those who persevere in sin are those who are held in abhorrence by God, but those who abandon the ways of sin are loved by the Lord.', 62829, 0), (463143, 'He who is unable to live in society, or who has no need because he is sufficient for himself, must be either a beast or a god.', 1116, 0), (463144, 'God does not die on the day when we cease to believe in a personal deity, but we die on the day when our lives cease to be illumined by the steady radiance, renewed daily, of a wonder, the source of which is beyond all reason.', 851, 0), (463145, 'When I judge art, I take my painting and put it next to a God made object like a tree or flower. If it clashes, it is not art.', 19754, 0), (463146, 'God''s finger touched him, and he slept.', 63203, 0), (463147, 'God grants liberty only to those who love it, and are always ready to guard and defend it.', 3308, 0), (463148, 'Apply yourself. Get all the education you can, but then, by God, do something. Don''t just stand there, make it happen.', 11247, 0), (463149, 'Men judge us by the success of our efforts. God looks at the efforts themselves.', 42, 0), (463150, 'I consider myself very lucky. God has a funny way of bringing some things around and knocking you in the head with the ultimate destination. Something I should have achieved quite easily took me a long time to get around to. It came in His time, not mine.', 7414, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (463151, 'God has been very good to me, for I never dwell upon anything wrong which a person has done, so as to remember it afterwards. If I do remember it, I always see some other virtue in that person.', 69044, 0), (463152, 'I have learned that to have a good friend is the purest of all God''s gifts, for it is a love that has no exchange of payment.', 52944, 0), (463153, 'It is clear that he does not pray, who, far from uplifting himself to God, requires that God shall lower Himself to him, and who resorts to prayer not to stir the man in us to will what God wills, but only to persuade God to will what the man in us wills.', 1539, 0), (463154, 'God is not a dead equation!', 8809, 0), (463155, 'God is in all men, but all men are not in God; that is why we suffer.', 4269, 0), (463156, 'You and I are but specks of that rhythmic urge which is Brahma, which is Allah, which is God.', 59887, 0), (463157, 'God wants us to prosper financially, to have plenty of money, to fulfill the destiny He has laid out for us.', 3956, 0), (463158, 'I always had a desire to know asylum life more thoroughly - a desire to be convinced that the most helpless of God''s creatures, the insane, were cared for kindly and properly.', 72002, 0), (463159, 'When I was doing theater, I was very successful at believing that I was great, God''s gift to the theater.', 30247, 0), (463160, 'If you have God on your side, everything becomes clear.', 31997, 0), (463161, 'The highest revelation is that God is in every man.', 760, 0), (463162, 'Man is to man either a god or a wolf.', 67390, 0), (463163, 'God doesn''t seek for golden vessels, and does not ask for silver ones, but He must have clean ones.', 3200, 0), (463164, 'The highest reward that God gives us for good work is the ability to do better work.', 4, 0), (463165, 'A singer starts by having his instrument as a gift from God... When you have been given something in a moment of grace, it is sacrilegious to be greedy.', 15432, 0), (463166, 'Two days after moving we recommended ourselves to God, Our Lord, and fled, hoping that, although it was late in the season and the fruits of the tunas were giving out, by remaining in the field we might still get over a good portion of the land.', 71377, 0), (463167, 'Jail didn''t make me find God, He''s always been there. They can lock me up, but my spirit and my love can never be confined to prison walls.', 2080, 0), (463168, 'Basically, there are two paths you can walk: faith or fear. It''s impossible to simultaneously trust God and not trust God.', 67762, 0), (463169, 'Now the only way you can serve God on earth is by serving others.', 710, 0), (463170, 'God has never made a mistake. Ever.', 45107, 0), (463171, 'God''s forgiveness allows us to be honest with ourselves. We recognize our imperfections, admit our failures, and plead to God for clemency.', 4059, 0), (463172, 'Have you ever struggled to find work or love, only to find them after you have given up? This is the paradox of letting go. Let go, in order to achieve. Letting go is God''s law.', 1055, 0), (463173, 'It''s not about being thin, it''s about being healthy. And when you are a child you like to eat all these unhealthy things like chocolate and sweets. Oh my God. I love strawberries dipped in chocolate and Lion bars and Toffee Crisps - and as you grow up, you have to learn that those things are only good in moderation or you will become very fat.', 73514, 0), (463174, 'The tragedy of life and of the world is not that men do not know God; the tragedy is that, knowing Him, they still insist on going their own way.', 18978, 0), (463175, 'Do not compare yourself. Find out what God has placed in your ability.', 68118, 0), (463176, 'When I took the habit, the Lord immediately showed me how He favours those who do violence to themselves in order to serve Him. No one saw what I endured... At the moment of my entrance into this new state I felt a joy so great that it has never failed me even to this day; and God converted the dryness of my soul into a very great tenderness.', 69044, 0), (463177, 'I am blessed to receive a word from God every day in receiving the scriptures and reading the scriptures. And God speaks through the Bible.', 66992, 0), (463178, 'God is most glorified in us when we are most satisfied in Him.', 1395, 0), (463179, 'The word ''God'' usually signifies ''Lord'', but every lord is not a God. It is the dominion of a spiritual being which constitutes a God: a true, supreme, or imaginary dominion makes a true, supreme, or imaginary God.', 2482, 0), (463180, 'I do not believe that God has created us under this dire necessity to toil, like beasts, to sustain life. I believe it is his will that we should hold absolute mastery over time, so as to devote it mainly to intellectual and moral improvement, domestic enjoyment, and social intercourse.', 55740, 0), (463181, 'There are two kinds of people one can call reasonable: those who serve God with all their heart because they know him, and those who seek him with all their heart because they do not know him.', 144, 0), (463182, 'God doesn''t want us to have rigid rituals with Him. In the new covenant, He is more interested in having a relationship with us.', 52414, 0), (463183, 'God expects but one thing of you, and that is that you should come out of yourself in so far as you are a created being made and let God be God in you.', 418, 0), (463184, 'With all the media attention, all the love from the fans, I felt I needed to prove myself. Prove that I''m not a marketing tool, I''m not a ploy to improve attendance. Prove I can play in this league. But I''ve surrendered that to God. I''m not in a battle with what everybody else thinks anymore.', 69766, 0), (463185, 'It is easy for Christians to have the false impression that once we have established a relationship with Christ, which we believe sets us right with God, the problems of life will somehow scoot away or they will slowly be removed from our lives.', 1789, 0), (463186, 'Every creature is a word of God.', 418, 0), (463187, 'The grace of God is dangerous. It''s lavish, excessive, outrageous, and scandalous. God''s grace is ridiculously inclusive. Apparently God doesn''t care who He loves. He is not very careful about the people He calls His friends or the people He calls His Church.', 16455, 0), (463188, 'Conscience is the authentic voice of God to you.', 37393, 0), (463189, 'God knows I detest slavery but it is an existing evil, and we must endure it and give it such protection as is guaranteed by the Constitution.', 58652, 0), (463190, 'I''m always happy for people when I see God blessing them the way he''s blessed me.', 38476, 0), (463191, 'Men must be governed by God or they will be ruled by tyrants.', 3256, 0), (463192, 'The feeling of longing for home is born into us. That wonderful dream cannot become real without great faith - enough for the Holy Ghost to lead us to repentance, baptism, and the making and keeping of sacred covenants with God. This faith requires enduring bravely the trials of mortal life.', 9158, 0), (463193, 'The Eucharistic mystery stands at the heart and center of the liturgy since it is the fount of life by which we are cleansed and strengthened to live not for ourselves but for God and to be united in love among ourselves.', 3779, 0), (463194, 'But this will not do, God will certainly punish you for stealing and for being unfaithful.', 73515, 0), (463195, 'I''m black because I was born this way. I''m proud of it. Thank God I am who I am.', 69332, 0), (463196, 'Not only is there no God, but try finding a plumber on Sunday.', 281, 0), (463197, 'The wonderful news is that our Lord is a God of mercy, and He responds to repentance.', 4008, 0), (463198, 'Grow in the root of all grace, which is faith. Believe God''s promises more firmly than ever. Allow your faith to increase in its fullness, firmness, and simplicity.', 36532, 0), (463199, 'You can only learn so much from books. You can only learn so much from education. Ultimately, it is the wisdom of God that will carry you through in the toughest situations of life.', 4001, 0), (463200, 'I wake up every day inspiring myself, because God gave me life.', 68176, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (463201, 'Your faithfulness makes you trustworthy to God.', 12361, 0), (463202, 'Bitterness and unforgiveness block the flow of God''s blessing in your life and actually hinder your prayers.', 58655, 0), (463203, 'Man was created to praise, reverence, and serve God our Lord and in this way to save his soul. The other things on Earth were created for man''s use, to help him reach the end for which he was created.', 70538, 0), (463204, 'I like to go dancing, have a few beers. I like being alone, too. I have days where it''s ''God, get me a shot of tequila.''', 71874, 0), (463205, 'It''s a mystery. That''s the first thing that interests me about the idea of God. If there is one, it''s mysterious and powerful and awesome to even consider the concept, and you have to take it seriously.', 578, 0), (463206, 'A faithful woman can become a devoted daughter of God - more concerned with being righteous than with being selfish, more anxious to exercise compassion than to exercise dominion, more committed to integrity than to notoriety. And she knows of her own infinite worth.', 71238, 0), (463207, 'God gave me a voice to sing with, and when you have that, what other gimmick is there?', 15469, 0), (463208, 'If you need me to tell you that if you serve God, you''ll get a Mercedes, you''re lost.', 69572, 0), (463209, 'My mama told me in college, ''I love you, and you''re God''s child, but natural beauty will only take you so far.''', 26560, 0), (463210, 'I don''t really know why I care so much. I just have something inside me that tells me that there is a problem, and I have got to do something about it. I think that is what I would call the God in me.', 17733, 0), (463211, 'Ascetics and fakirs come to mitigate human suffering to heal us and lead us on the path. They put up with criticism they go through many worldly trials. Some of them have even become martyrs for our sake. But they have done all this with a smile and with gratitude to God. Hence sacrifice is a great virtue.', 69021, 0), (463212, 'As we lay hold upon the truth of God, its influence must affect us. It must elevate us. It must remove from us every imperfection.', 4150, 0), (463213, 'It doesn''t matter who likes you or doesn''t like you, all that matters is that God likes you. He accepts you, he approves of you.', 3956, 0), (463214, 'The sin which is indulged to the greatest extent, which separates us from God and produces so many spiritual disorders, and which are contagious, is selfishness.', 4150, 0), (463215, 'Whatsoever is done out of pure love, be it ever so little or contemptible in the sight of men, is wholly fruitful; for God measures more with how much love one worketh, than the amount he doeth.', 4150, 0), (463216, 'When your identity is found in Christ, your identity never changes. You are always a child of God.', 4052, 0), (463217, 'All God wants of man is a peaceful heart.', 418, 0), (463218, 'As much as I loved the model of St. Francis, I realized that I couldn''t afford to be poor, because unlike St. Francis, I''m not celibate. I was enlightened that God''s call to me was not poverty but generosity and simplicity. And I had to go back to the lesson I learned from my parents: that is, simplicity.', 9129, 0), (463219, 'The greatest legacy is that which benefits the widest number of people for the longest period without limit to value. No one but the Prophet Muhammad was given that role as the seal of God''s message.', 61043, 0), (463220, 'He who desires to worship God must harbor no childish illusions about the matter but bravely renounce his liberty and humanity.', 3973, 0), (463221, 'God is the most ancient of all things, for he had no birth.', 64386, 0), (463222, 'Other people - they practice and they practice... these fingers of mine, they got brains in ''em. You don''t tell them what to do - they do it. God given talent.', 3401, 0), (463223, 'If triangles had a god, they would give him three sides.', 48659, 0), (463224, 'There were times, especially when I was traveling for ''Eat, Pray, Love,'' when, I swear to God, I would feel this weight of my female ancestors, all those Swedish farmwives from beyond the grave who were like, ''Go! Go to Naples! Eat more pizza! Go to India, ride an elephant! Do it! Swim in the Indian Ocean. Read those books. Learn a language.''', 20, 0), (463225, 'That the saints may enjoy their beatitude and the grace of God more abundantly they are permitted to see the punishment of the damned in hell.', 1539, 0), (463226, 'TO fear God, is one of the first and greatest Duties of his rational Creatures.', 68734, 0), (463227, 'Einstein, stop telling God what to do!', 2826, 0), (463228, 'Today I love myself as I love my god: who could charge me with a sin today? I know only sins against my god but who knows my god?', 11, 0), (463229, 'There''s always an element of self delusion among people who believe they ought to be President. There''s an underestimation of your opponent and an overestimation of your own abilities. This is compatible with being rich and powerful, the idea that we were blessed by God because we deserve to be blessed.', 1229, 0), (463230, 'For me, Batman is the one that can most clearly be taken seriously. He''s not from another planet, or filled with radioactive gunk. I mean, Superman is essentially a god, but Batman is more like Hercules: he''s a human being, very flawed, and bridges the divide.', 11711, 0), (463231, 'We esteem, honor, and love the apostles more than the other saints, because they served God more faithfully and because they loved Him more perfectly.', 70538, 0), (463232, 'I fear God and next to God I mostly fear them that fear him not.', 4010, 0), (463233, 'God''s most lordly gift to man is decency of mind.', 1882, 0), (463234, 'One of the peculiar sins of the twentieth century which we''ve developed to a very high level is the sin of credulity. It has been said that when human beings stop believing in God 